    "description": "After slowly getting used to the monotony of the hospital, a letter is placed gently in front of you...<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3172480/extras/1c4591e853e09e1500e4d161faf4b1de.avif?t=1729762514\" width=600 height=600 /></span><br><br>The scrawl is as embarrassed about its content as the old woman is to have burdened you with it.<br>It reads:<br><br>We are all so glad to hear about your swift recovery, the state of drivers these days worry us all!<br>Please can you continue towards that stead, the old pastor's ever so ill and we hear he's not got long left.<br>We know this is a big ask, with your condition, but this is a delicate congregation, no sense on how to be without their spiritual guide.<br><br>She stares, interrogating blinks trying to tease out your faculties.<br><br>You won't get another opportunity like this.<br>This is perfect.<br><br><br><br><strong>The Parish</strong> is a slow-burning, atmospheric horror game about tackling the mysteries of this church, its people and its founder, preferably all while staying alive.<br><br><strong>Game features:</strong><br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Lots of drab, awkward conversations not at all inspired by real life<br></li><li>The ability to <strong>sprint</strong> away from the beasties!<br></li><li>Multiple Endings reflecting your choices during the story!<br></li><li> The rich culture and wildlife around the parish (If you can find any)<br></li><li>Free access to the old man's pain medication! (just don't tell him)<br></li><li>The ability to choose what sermons you give!<br></li><li>The ability to resist devilish temptation by abstaining in a corner of the world!<br></li><li>A door that can be bolted and locked during the night!</li></ul>",
